For n \geq  0, we assume by induction that being n-1-truncated is a proposition to prove that being n-truncated is a proposition. In other words, we must show that \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
